WEBVTT

00:06.800 --> 00:09.667
YOU'RE DEAD,
SPENCER.

00:12.580 --> 00:13.569
WHAT YOU DOING, SHAWN?

00:13.610 --> 00:14.679
NOTHING.

00:14.710 --> 00:15.529
LOOKS LIKE SOMETHING TO ME.

00:15.580 --> 00:16.478
[SIGHING]: OKAY.

00:16.510 --> 00:19.115
I WAS RUNNING AWAY
FROM RYAN BRICKHOUSE.

00:19.150 --> 00:20.242
THAT HIM?

00:20.280 --> 00:21.110
UH-HUH.

00:21.150 --> 00:22.219
IS HE THE SAME KID

00:22.250 --> 00:23.615
WHO'S BEEN HASSLING YOU
ALL WEEK?

00:23.650 --> 00:25.686
YEAH.

00:28.190 --> 00:30.658
AND WHY IS HE
CHASING YOU TODAY?

00:30.690 --> 00:32.794
I MIGHT HAVE
THROWN A ROCK AT HIM.

00:34.200 --> 00:35.599
DID YOU HIT HIM?

00:35.630 --> 00:36.699
ALMOST.

00:39.700 --> 00:41.065
GET BACK OUT THERE.

00:41.100 --> 00:42.328
WHAT?

00:42.370 --> 00:44.565
CAN'T RUN AWAY
FROM THE BAD GUYS FOREVER.

00:44.610 --> 00:46.077
EVENTUALLY, YOU'VE GOT TO
COME UP WITH A NEW APPROACH.

00:46.110 --> 00:47.577
SO...

00:47.610 --> 00:50.408
SO...FIND ONE.

00:59.490 --> 01:00.684
YOU'RE FLUNKING MATH?

01:00.720 --> 01:01.709
PROUDLY.

01:02.890 --> 01:04.255
HERE'S THE DEAL--

01:04.290 --> 01:05.552
LEAVE ME ALONE,

01:05.590 --> 01:07.626
I'LL MAKE SURE
YOU ACE THE TEST TOMORROW.

01:07.660 --> 01:08.854
HOW?

01:08.900 --> 01:10.561
EVERY THIRD ANSWER IS "C".

01:10.600 --> 01:13.569
THERE'S A PA'I'I'ERN
TO ALL HER TESTS.

01:13.600 --> 01:15.591
MRS. BODANSKY
DOES IT EVERY TIME.

01:15.640 --> 01:16.766
I MEMORIZED IT.
I'LL SHOW YOU.

01:16.810 --> 01:19.608
YOU BE'I'I'ER NOT BE LYING.

01:22.780 --> 01:23.747
NOT BAD.

01:23.780 --> 01:24.747
YOU FACED YOUR FEARS.

01:24.780 --> 01:25.747
YOU GOT A NEW RESULT.

01:25.780 --> 01:27.816
YOU CAME OUT
AHEAD.

01:27.850 --> 01:30.239
DID YOU REALLY MEMORIZE
THOSE TEST ANSWERS?

01:30.290 --> 01:31.348
YEAH.

01:35.190 --> 01:36.748
[EXHALING]

01:36.790 --> 01:38.428
WHO ARE YOU CALLING?

01:38.460 --> 01:39.757
[RINGING]

01:39.800 --> 01:41.597
YOUR MATH TEACHER.

01:42.770 --> 01:46.297
[VIDEO GAME BEEPING]

01:51.510 --> 01:52.636
NO. NO. NO.

01:52.680 --> 01:54.204
NO. YES.

01:54.240 --> 01:55.776
YES...

01:55.810 --> 01:57.846
NICKEL--
THAT'S A NICKEL.

01:57.880 --> 01:59.768
YES. YES. YES.

01:59.820 --> 02:02.345
WHO WAS THAT?
WHO WAS WHO?

02:02.390 --> 02:03.641
THE GIRL SITTING
AT OUR FRONT DESK.

02:03.690 --> 02:05.578
YOU'RE TALKING
ABOUT THE LOVELY DAGMAR.

02:05.620 --> 02:06.712
DAG MAR?

02:06.760 --> 02:07.818
SHE'S OUR NEW RECEPTIONIST.

02:07.860 --> 02:08.815
HOW DID SHE GET THE JOB?

02:08.860 --> 02:09.929
THE AGENCY
SENT HER OVER.

02:09.960 --> 02:11.655
YOU CONTACTED
A TEMP AGENCY

02:11.690 --> 02:12.827
WITHOUT CONSULTING ME?

02:12.860 --> 02:14.498
GUS, ANYONE CAN
GET A SECRETARY

02:14.530 --> 02:15.622
FROM A TEMP AGENCY.

02:15.660 --> 02:17.161
IT TAKES REAL FORESIGHT
AND CREATIVITY

02:17.200 --> 02:18.360
TO GET ONE FROM
A MODELING AGENCY.

02:18.400 --> 02:20.698
A MODELING AGENCY?

02:22.440 --> 02:24.328
WOW.

02:24.370 --> 02:26.679
NOW, WHY WOULD
A BEAUTIFUL LADY LIKE THAT

02:26.710 --> 02:28.632
WANT TO BE OUR SECRETARY?

02:28.680 --> 02:30.443
[GAME CHIRPS]

02:30.480 --> 02:31.777
OH, THAT'S A BIT
OF A STORY, YOU SEE.

02:31.810 --> 02:33.846
APPARENTLY,
SHE GOT IT IN HER HEAD

02:33.880 --> 02:36.189
THAT THIS
WAS A RUNWAY GIG.

02:36.220 --> 02:37.187
I BLAME THE AGENT.

02:37.220 --> 02:38.187
I WAS VERY CLEAR
ON THE PHONE.

02:38.220 --> 02:39.517
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

02:39.560 --> 02:40.515
BUT SHE'S COOL
WITH STICKING AROUND

02:40.560 --> 02:41.515
FOR THE REST OF THE DAY,

02:41.560 --> 02:42.527
SEEING HOW IT GOES.

02:42.560 --> 02:43.527
YOU KNOW
HOW SLOW IT GETS

02:43.560 --> 02:44.686
WHEN IT'S NOT
MODELING SEASON.

02:44.730 --> 02:46.527
DOES SHE ANSWER
THE PHONE?

02:46.560 --> 02:47.629
YES, BUT ONLY HER CELL PHONE.

02:47.660 --> 02:48.729
SHE'S EXPECTING A CALL
FROM MILAN.

02:48.760 --> 02:49.966
DOES SHE FILE?

02:50.000 --> 02:51.592
MOSTLY HER NAILS.

02:51.630 --> 02:52.164
COFFEE?

02:52.200 --> 02:53.462
YEAH, SHE WANTS SOME.

02:53.500 --> 02:54.728
CAN I MAKE YOU ANYTHING?

02:54.770 --> 02:55.839
NO.

02:55.870 --> 02:56.962
[RINGING]

02:57.010 --> 02:58.739
DUDE, I THOUGHT
YOU WEREN'T COMING IN

02:58.770 --> 02:59.839
TILL, LIKE, NOON?

02:59.880 --> 03:00.801
BIG DRAMA AT THE OFFICE TODAY.

03:00.840 --> 03:02.649
A DOCTOR WE SUPPLY PRODUCT TO
GOT KILLED.

03:02.680 --> 03:03.669
WHOA!

03:03.710 --> 03:04.699
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

03:04.750 --> 03:05.739
YOU DIDN'T CALL ME IMMEDIATELY?

03:05.780 --> 03:06.769
YOU DON'T KNOW HIM.

03:06.820 --> 03:07.741
THIS IS WHAT WE DO, REMEMBER?

03:07.780 --> 03:08.678
WE CAN SOLVE THE CASE.

03:08.720 --> 03:09.880
THE POLICE ARE ALREADY THERE.

03:09.920 --> 03:10.887
THIS MEANS NOTHING TO ME.

03:10.920 --> 03:12.410
THEY'RE GOING TO NEED HELP.

03:12.460 --> 03:13.779
GUIDANCE.
PSYCHIC VIBRATIONS.

03:15.360 --> 03:16.657
DAG MAR!

03:16.690 --> 03:17.827
OH!

03:17.860 --> 03:19.521
[SPEAKING GERMAN]

03:19.560 --> 03:21.221
[SPEAKS GERMAN]

03:21.260 --> 03:24.718
SHE DOESN'T SPEAK ENGLISH?

03:24.770 --> 03:26.590
DOES SHE NEED TO?

03:31.610 --> 03:33.498
WHERE IN THE NAME
OF ALL THAT IS HOLY

03:33.540 --> 03:35.269
IS MY FORENSICS TEAM?

03:35.310 --> 03:37.699
ALL RIGHT, WHAT CAN YOU TELL ME
ABOUT THIS DOCTOR

03:37.750 --> 03:39.741
THAT I CAN PRETEND TO ASCERTAIN
FROM THE SPIRIT WORLD?

03:39.780 --> 03:40.769
DR. BLINN WASN'T
ON MY ROUTE.

03:40.820 --> 03:42.640
I DID COVER HIM
A FEW TIMES.

03:42.690 --> 03:43.714
ALL I REMEMBER

03:43.750 --> 03:45.240
IS HE ALWAYS
MADE YOU WAIT,

03:45.290 --> 03:46.587
AND HE HAD AN PICTURE
OF PETE ROSE ON HIS WALL.

03:46.620 --> 03:47.814
LOOK HOW CUTE SHE IS
IN THE FUCHSIA.

03:50.730 --> 03:52.459
I HAVE BEEN SENT
BY THE SPIRIT OF PETE ROSE.

03:52.500 --> 03:53.421
PETE ROSE ISN'T DEAD.

03:53.460 --> 03:55.724
THERE WAS A PHOTO OF PETE ROSE
ON THE WALL.

03:55.760 --> 03:56.761
OKAY, WHY HAVE I BEEN
DRAWN HERE?

03:56.800 --> 03:57.824
WAS THERE A MURDER?

03:57.870 --> 03:59.599
DO I NEED THE LITTLE BOOTIES
FOR THE CRIME SCENE?

03:59.640 --> 04:02.859
THANKS, BUT WE'RE DOING
JUST FINE.

04:05.810 --> 04:07.368
DON'T GO IN THE BACK ROOM.

04:09.810 --> 04:11.698
MY GRANDPA
LOVED PETE ROSE.

04:11.750 --> 04:13.047
I WANT YOU GUYS
RINGING DOORBELLS.

04:13.080 --> 04:14.479
IF ANYBODY SAW ANYTHING,
I WANT TO KNOW ABOUT IT.

04:14.520 --> 04:15.669
PATIENT FILES?

04:15.720 --> 04:16.948
CABINET'S LOCKED.
WE HAVEN'T FOUND THE KEY.

04:16.990 --> 04:18.412
GET AHOLD
OF THE D.A.'S OFFICE.

04:18.450 --> 04:19.758
TELL THEM I NEED
ACCESS TO THOSE FILES.

04:19.790 --> 04:21.712
IF THEY SAY WE NEED
A WARRANT, GET IT.

04:21.760 --> 04:23.682
ALSO, GET ME A COPY
OF HIS DESK CALENDAR.

04:25.460 --> 04:27.496
I THOUGHT I TOLD YOU NO.

04:27.530 --> 04:28.827
BUT YOUR EYES
SAID YES.

04:28.860 --> 04:31.567
HEY, WHO'S
THAT CINCINNATI RED

04:31.600 --> 04:33.431
WITH THE BOWL CUT?

04:37.610 --> 04:40.636
LET ME BE PERFECT LY CLEAR.

04:40.680 --> 04:41.704
THIS IS MY CRIME SCENE.

04:41.740 --> 04:42.877
I DON'T NEED
YOUR HELP.

04:42.910 --> 04:44.502
I DON'T WANT
YOUR HELP.

04:44.550 --> 04:45.505
IF YOU DON'T
LEAVE RIGHT NOW,

04:45.550 --> 04:46.471
I WILL HAVE YOU ARRESTED

04:46.520 --> 04:47.817
FOR INTERFERING
WITH A POLICE INVESTIGATION.

04:47.850 --> 04:49.317
AM I CLEAR?

04:49.350 --> 04:51.409
LIKE BUTTER.

04:57.860 --> 05:00.454
I'VE GIVEN THIS
A GREAT DEAL OF THOUGHT.

05:00.500 --> 05:02.092
I THINK WE SHOULD
TAKE THE REST OF THE DAY OFF.

05:02.130 --> 05:03.722
WHAT SAY YOU?

05:03.770 --> 05:05.795
ALL WE'VE DONE IS EAT
A BOX OF ANIMAL COOKIES

05:05.830 --> 05:06.990
AND CRASH A CRIME SCENE.

05:07.040 --> 05:08.496
THE CASE
WITH THE DOCTOR--

05:08.540 --> 05:09.461
THEY'RE COMING BACK TO US
EVENTUALLY.

05:09.510 --> 05:10.636
YOU KNOW THIS.

05:10.670 --> 05:11.602
SO LET'S GO
TO THE BEACH.

05:11.640 --> 05:13.369
IT'S TOO NICE A DAY
FOR MURDER AND MAYHEM.

05:13.410 --> 05:14.707
[DOOR OPENS]

05:14.740 --> 05:16.446
I HAVE TO SEE THEM
HT NOW--

05:16.480 --> 05:17.640
IT'S IMPORTANT.

05:17.680 --> 05:18.749
I'M SORRY.

05:18.780 --> 05:19.815
I DON'T MEAN
TO BARGE IN, BUT...

05:20.720 --> 05:21.778
I NEED HELP.

05:24.590 --> 05:25.784
[SHAWN]: MR. DUNN...
ROBERT...

05:25.820 --> 05:26.980
HOW CAN WE HELP?

05:27.020 --> 05:28.749
AND CAN I CALL YOU "BOB"?

05:28.790 --> 05:30.587
THIS IS DIFFICULT.

05:30.630 --> 05:31.449
TAKE YOUR TIME.

05:31.490 --> 05:32.718
WE'RE HERE.

05:32.760 --> 05:35.752
I'M JUST GOING TO COME OUT
AND SAY IT.

05:35.800 --> 05:37.665
[SIGHING]

05:37.700 --> 05:38.894
I'M BEING HAUNTED.

05:38.930 --> 05:40.431
HAUNTED?

05:40.470 --> 05:41.664
YES.

05:41.700 --> 05:43.839
THERE'S A HAUNTING...

05:43.870 --> 05:45.531
[MOUTHING WORDS]

05:45.570 --> 05:46.969
GUS, CAN I TALK
TO YOU OUTSIDE?

05:47.010 --> 05:48.034
WE'RE IN THE MIDDLE
OF SOMETHING.

05:48.080 --> 05:48.876
GUS.

05:48.910 --> 05:49.672
STOP TALKING. SIT DOWN.

05:49.710 --> 05:51.575
NOW, WHAT EXACTLY

05:51.610 --> 05:54.044
DO YOU MEAN
WHEN YOU SAY "HAUNTED"?

05:54.080 --> 05:56.514
WELL...

05:56.550 --> 05:57.915
MY HOME...

05:57.950 --> 05:59.679
SOMETIMES
I SMELL PERFUME

05:59.720 --> 06:01.756
WHEN NO ONE ELSE
IS AROUND.

06:01.790 --> 06:03.553
THINGS GET BROKEN
OR MOVED.

06:03.590 --> 06:04.727
[CELL PHONE VIBRATING]

06:04.760 --> 06:05.624
I THINK YOU HAVE
A TEST MESSAGE.

06:05.660 --> 06:06.991
I'LL GET IT LATER.

06:07.030 --> 06:07.826
I THINK YOU SHOULD
GET IT NOW.

06:16.040 --> 06:17.667
SORRY.

06:17.710 --> 06:19.029
WORK BUSINESS.

06:19.070 --> 06:20.139
OKAY...

06:21.840 --> 06:23.171
CAN I ASK YOU A QUESTION?

06:23.210 --> 06:24.677
YEAH.

06:24.710 --> 06:27.713
DO THESE SPIRITS EVER
SPEAK TO YOU?

06:27.750 --> 06:28.842
NO. NO.

06:28.880 --> 06:30.939
WHATEVER--
WHOEVER IT IS,

06:30.990 --> 06:32.855
IT HASN'T
SPOKEN TO ME.

06:32.890 --> 06:33.857
OH.

06:33.890 --> 06:35.448
HAVE YOU CONTACTED THE POLICE?

06:35.490 --> 06:37.128
YEAH,
BUT THEY SAID

06:37.160 --> 06:38.479
THERE WAS NOTHING THEY COULD DO.

06:38.530 --> 06:40.521
SO HERE I AM.

06:40.560 --> 06:41.959
[CELL PHONE VIBRATING]

06:42.000 --> 06:43.763
ROBERT, WE DEAL
WITH THIS KIND OF PHENOMENON

06:43.800 --> 06:45.563
ALL THE TIME,

06:45.600 --> 06:46.965
AND WHAT YOU NEED
TO REALIZE

06:47.000 --> 06:47.967
IS THAT EVICTING
A SPIRIT

06:48.000 --> 06:50.730
IS A VERY
TIME-CONSUMING

06:50.770 --> 06:52.032
AND ABSURDLY
EXPENSIVE PROCESS.

06:52.070 --> 06:53.833
I DON'T CARE, OKAY?

06:53.880 --> 06:55.768
I JUST CAN'T GO ON
LIVING THIS WAY.

06:55.810 --> 06:56.799
[CELL PHONE CHIRPS]

06:56.850 --> 06:57.748
EXCUSE ME.

06:59.750 --> 07:00.648
OH, REALLY?

07:00.680 --> 07:02.580
YES!
YES, SHAWN.

07:02.620 --> 07:04.986
ALL I'M SAYING IS THAT
IT MIGHT BE EASIER

07:05.020 --> 07:06.817
TO TRY MOVING INTO
A DIFFERENT HOUSE.

07:06.860 --> 07:09.078
ONE THAT'S LESS...
HAUNTED.

07:09.120 --> 07:10.826
I TRIED THAT.

07:10.860 --> 07:11.827
WHATEVER THIS THING IS,

07:11.860 --> 07:13.452
IT FOLLOWED ME
ALL THE WAY FROM SAN FRANCISCO.

07:13.500 --> 07:14.489
MAYBE IT LIKES YOU.

07:14.530 --> 07:16.669
NO. I DON'T THINK SO.

07:16.700 --> 07:18.429
WHAT MAKES YOU
SAY THAT?

07:20.570 --> 07:21.764
I THINK
IT TRIED TO KILL ME.

07:24.910 --> 07:28.038
[***]

07:28.080 --> 07:32.471
* I KNOW YOU KNOW
THAT I'M NOT TELLING THE TRUTH *

07:32.520 --> 07:34.943
* I KNOW YOU KNOW
THEY JUST DON'T HAVE ANY PROOF *

07:34.980 --> 07:36.743
* EMBRACE THE DECEPTION

07:36.790 --> 07:38.610
* LEARN HOW TO BEND

07:38.650 --> 07:40.481
* YOUR WORST INHIBITIONS

07:40.520 --> 07:43.080
* THEY WILL PSYCH YOU OUT
IN THE END **

07:50.970 --> 07:53.063
GUS, WHAT IS ALL THIS?

07:53.100 --> 07:55.136
GEAR WE MIGHT NEED.

07:55.170 --> 07:56.660
IF WE'RE GOING TO BE
HUNTING FOR SPIRITS,

07:56.710 --> 07:57.938
WE MIGHT AS WELL
DO IT RIGHT.

07:57.970 --> 07:59.608
METHODICALLY,
SYSTEMATICALLY,

07:59.640 --> 08:00.777
SCIENTIFICALLY.

08:00.810 --> 08:01.879
WHO KNOWS,

08:01.910 --> 08:03.775
WE MIGHT BE SURPRISED
WHAT WE FIND.

08:03.810 --> 08:05.072
VIDEO CAMERA, NICE.

08:05.110 --> 08:06.202
AUDIO RECORDER.

08:06.250 --> 08:07.808
MOTION DETECTORS.

08:07.850 --> 08:08.874
GUS, I AM
VERY IMPRESSED.

08:08.920 --> 08:10.911
YOU ONLY FORGOT
ONE THING.

08:10.950 --> 08:12.087
REALLY? WHAT?

08:12.120 --> 08:14.588
THERE'S NO SUCH THING
AS GHOSTS.

08:14.620 --> 08:15.712
YES, THERE IS.

08:15.760 --> 08:16.954
OH, GUS, NO.

08:16.990 --> 08:18.924
OKAY.

08:18.960 --> 08:20.291
STOP. PLEASE.

08:20.330 --> 08:22.252
LET'S JUST...
LET'S JUST STOP.

08:22.300 --> 08:23.824
COME HERE, SIT DOWN.

08:23.870 --> 08:24.825
PLEASE. SIT.

08:28.270 --> 08:29.862
ALL RIGHT.

08:29.910 --> 08:31.764
THIS IS ME TALKING.
THIS IS SHAWN.

08:31.810 --> 08:32.936
WHAT'S GOING ON?

08:32.980 --> 08:33.935
I USUALLY HAVE TO DRAG YOU
TO THESE CASES

08:33.980 --> 08:35.072
KICKING AND SCREAMING,

08:35.110 --> 08:36.668
AND THOSE ARE REAL POLICE CASES.

08:36.710 --> 08:37.642
NOW, ALL OF A SUDDEN,

08:37.680 --> 08:40.012
WE HAVE SOME CLIENT
WHO IS EITHER BONKERS,

08:40.050 --> 08:41.972
OR, JUDGING BY THE SIZE
OF THE BAGS UNDER HIS EYES,

08:42.020 --> 08:43.647
SUFFERING FROM NOTHING MORE
THAN WAKING DREAMS

08:43.690 --> 08:44.611
OR HALLUCINATIONS,

08:44.650 --> 08:47.050
AND YOU, YOU'RE READY
TO GO GHOST-HUNTING.

08:48.820 --> 08:49.821
TALK TO ME.

08:49.860 --> 08:51.987
ALL RIGHT.

08:53.100 --> 08:54.829
ALL RIGHT.

08:54.860 --> 08:56.919
I'VE NEVER TOLD THIS
TO ANYONE BEFORE,

08:56.970 --> 08:58.562
BUT...

08:58.600 --> 09:00.568
I WAS 12.

09:00.600 --> 09:01.669
[SIGHING]

09:01.700 --> 09:03.167
GUS, IT'S ME.

09:05.970 --> 09:07.733
IT WAS LATE.

09:07.780 --> 09:10.203
I WAS IN MY ROOM
WITH THE LIGHTS OFF.

09:10.250 --> 09:12.172
I HEARD A VOICE.

09:12.210 --> 09:13.575
GUS, I'M SURE

09:13.620 --> 09:14.973
THERE'S A PERFECT LY LOGICAL
EXPLANATION--

09:15.020 --> 09:16.169
NO, NO, NO, SHAWN.

09:16.220 --> 09:18.347
IT WASN'T ON TV
AND IT WASN'T A RADIO.

09:18.390 --> 09:19.755
IT WAS COMING FROM THE WALLS,

09:19.790 --> 09:21.212
AND THE VOICE...

09:21.260 --> 09:23.854
THE VOICE TOLD ME

09:23.890 --> 09:26.188
THAT OUR HOUSE WAS BUILT
ON AN OLD INDIAN BURIAL GROUND.

09:27.660 --> 09:28.854
SHUT UP.

09:28.900 --> 09:30.265
SHE SAID--

09:30.300 --> 09:32.029
SHE SAID SHE WAS SAD

09:32.070 --> 09:33.697
BECAUSE SHE HAD DIED
MANY MOONS AGO

09:33.740 --> 09:34.889
AND WAS TRAPPED BETWEEN WORLDS.

09:34.940 --> 09:36.828
WHEN I ASKED HER
HER NAME, SHAWN...

09:38.310 --> 09:40.301
SHE SAID...

09:42.040 --> 09:43.371
"MY NAM E--"

09:43.410 --> 09:44.741
[FEMININE VOICE]:
MY NAME IS WILTING FLOWER.

09:44.780 --> 09:48.079
I DIED WITHOUT
KNOWING LOVE.

09:48.120 --> 09:50.680
WILL YOU BE MY FRIEND?

09:51.790 --> 09:53.087
HOW-- HOW DID YOU KNOW THAT?

09:53.120 --> 09:55.008
I NEVER TOLD IT
TO ANYONE BEFORE!

09:55.060 --> 09:56.982
[NORMAL VOICE]:
I WAS WILTING FLOWER.

09:57.030 --> 09:59.055
GUS!

09:59.090 --> 10:01.320
I CAN'T BELIEVE
THAT YOU FELL FOR THAT!

10:01.360 --> 10:03.692
I PUT AN OLD WALKIE-TALKIE
IN THE WALL

10:03.730 --> 10:04.867
WHEN YOUR DAD...

10:04.900 --> 10:06.697
[SNICKERING]: WHEN YOUR DAD
PUT IN THE NEW INSULATION.

10:06.740 --> 10:08.890
THE OLD INDIAN
BURIAL GROUND?

10:08.940 --> 10:09.668
YOU BOUGHT THAT?

10:09.710 --> 10:11.735
I GOT THAT FROM POLTERGEIST...

10:11.770 --> 10:13.203
OR POLTERGEIST II.

10:13.240 --> 10:14.798
GREMLINS?

10:14.840 --> 10:16.239
NO, IT WASN'T
GREMLINS.

10:16.280 --> 10:18.248
THAT'S NOT FUNNY,
SHAWN.

10:18.280 --> 10:19.349
OKAY, YOU KNOW WHAT?

10:19.380 --> 10:21.348
LET'S ADD A "TRIXIE" TO THAT--

10:21.380 --> 10:24.213
NOW, SHE IS THE COMPANION
TO "SCRAPPY," RIGHT?

10:24.250 --> 10:27.754
OKAY, GREAT, LET'S ADD THAT
TO "GIRL WITH FLOWERS"

10:27.790 --> 10:29.212
AND "MERRY MUSICIANS."

10:29.260 --> 10:30.818
OKAY, NOW, LISTEN,

10:30.860 --> 10:34.296
I NEED THE CARD TO READ,
"HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

10:34.330 --> 10:38.721
'EX' IS THE LONELIEST LE'I'I'ER
IN THE ALPHABET."

10:38.770 --> 10:40.965
BUT I NEED YOU TO SPELL IT E-X,

10:41.000 --> 10:41.967
AS IN...

10:42.000 --> 10:44.059
OH, YOU GOT IT?

10:44.110 --> 10:45.907
OKAY, WELL, LISTEN,
IT CONTINUES...

10:45.940 --> 10:50.843
"FROM YOUIII}E |\)|(OT-YET-'EX"'--

10:53.480 --> 10:55.038
PERFECT.

10:55.080 --> 10:56.843
THESE'LL GO OUT TODAY, RIGHT?

10:56.890 --> 10:59.108
ALL RIGHTY-DIGHTY.
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

10:59.150 --> 11:02.119
I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU COLLECTED FIGURINES.

11:02.160 --> 11:03.149
YOU KNOW, I HAVE
A GRANDMOTHER WHO--

11:03.190 --> 11:04.225
DO YOU NOT KNOCK?

11:04.260 --> 11:06.125
THERE'S NO DOOR.

11:06.160 --> 11:07.798
AND?

11:07.830 --> 11:08.854
SORRY.

11:08.900 --> 11:10.094
THE D.A.'S OFFICE CALLED.

11:10.130 --> 11:11.165
THEY SAID THAT WE CAN
HAVE ACCESS

11:11.200 --> 11:12.269
TO DR. BLINN'S PATIENTS' FILES.

11:12.300 --> 11:14.234
ABOUT TIME.

11:14.270 --> 11:15.828
LET'S GET IN THERE,
GET THOSE ADDRESSES,

11:15.870 --> 11:17.428
AND BRING THESE NUTJOBS IN
FOR QUESTIONING.

11:19.940 --> 11:23.000
HERE'S WHERE I FOUND
ALL MY PAINTINGS LAST WEEKEND...

11:23.050 --> 11:24.108
[DEVICE BEEPING]

11:24.150 --> 11:25.469
UPSIDE DOWN.

11:25.510 --> 11:28.047
I'VE GOT A COLD SPOT.
RIGHT HERE.

11:28.080 --> 11:29.445
FEEL IT?

11:29.480 --> 11:31.744
YES. YES, I DO.

11:31.790 --> 11:33.951
ROBERT, WE'VE DEFINITELY
GOT SOMETHING HERE.

11:33.990 --> 11:36.379
YOU'RE STANDING
UNDER A VENT.

11:45.430 --> 11:47.466
SO ALL THESE ARE YOURS, HUH?

11:47.500 --> 11:49.036
YEAH.

11:49.070 --> 11:50.833
I'M TRYING TO GET READY
FOR A SHOW.

11:50.870 --> 11:52.064
NO KIDDING.

11:52.110 --> 11:53.998
HAS ANYTHING STRANGE
EVER HAPPENED IN HERE?

11:54.040 --> 11:55.439
SOMETIMES
I GET THE FEELING

11:55.480 --> 11:57.801
THAT THE FURNITURE
HAS BEEN MOVED.

11:57.850 --> 11:59.147
MM-HMM. MM-HMM.

11:59.180 --> 12:00.977
DID YOU ACTUALLY
SEE IT HAPPEN?

12:01.020 --> 12:02.942
NO, I JUST
COME INTO A ROOM

12:02.990 --> 12:05.185
AND EVERYTHING'S
NOT WHERE I LEFI' IT.

12:10.560 --> 12:13.825
ROBERT, DO YOU HAVE
A PHOTO ALBUM?

12:13.860 --> 12:15.498
YEAH.

12:17.930 --> 12:19.761
AH.

12:24.410 --> 12:25.900
THAT'S A NICE SHOT, HUH?

12:25.940 --> 12:28.033
OH. OH, OH, OH!

12:28.080 --> 12:29.172
I FEEL IT.

12:29.210 --> 12:31.974
I FEEL IT! OH, GUS! GUS!

12:32.010 --> 12:33.910
OH!

12:33.950 --> 12:35.076
OH, SHE IS ANGRY!

12:35.120 --> 12:36.212
SHE IS ANGRY!

12:36.250 --> 12:38.787
SHE IS SOARING
WITH RAGE AND--

12:38.820 --> 12:39.912
[SH RIEKING PRIMALLY]

12:39.960 --> 12:41.313
SHE WANTS TO GO
INTO THE BEDROOM!

12:41.360 --> 12:42.349
WHERE'S THE BEDROOM?

12:42.390 --> 12:43.823
IT'S HERE. HERE.
TAKE ME!

12:43.860 --> 12:45.919
OH!

12:47.400 --> 12:50.961
[SHAWN SHRIEKING PRIMALLY]

12:51.000 --> 12:53.230
[WHIMPERS]

12:53.270 --> 12:55.534
[RASPS]

12:55.570 --> 12:57.231
[BOOK THUDS]

12:58.570 --> 12:59.935
I'VE LOST HER.

12:59.980 --> 13:01.277
[SIGHING]

13:02.950 --> 13:04.406
YOU DON'T BELIEVE ME,
DO YOU?

13:04.450 --> 13:05.576
NO, OF COURSE WE DO.

13:05.610 --> 13:06.918
YOU SAW IT, TOO, DIDN'T YOU?

13:06.950 --> 13:08.918
GUYS.

13:08.950 --> 13:10.349
PLEASE.

13:10.390 --> 13:11.948
STAY THE NIGHT.

13:11.990 --> 13:13.309
THEN YOU'LL SEE.

13:13.360 --> 13:14.486
I MEAN, YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT IT'S BEEN LIKE.

13:14.520 --> 13:15.817
I CAN'T WORK.

13:15.860 --> 13:17.088
I CAN'T CONCENTRATE.

13:17.130 --> 13:18.950
I WAKE UP
IN THE MORNING

13:18.990 --> 13:19.957
MORE TIRED THAN
WHEN I WENT TO BED.

13:20.000 --> 13:20.989
DAYS PASS

13:21.030 --> 13:22.918
AND I CAN'T REMEMBER
WHAT I'VE DONE.

13:22.970 --> 13:24.096
UTHING WORDS]
[SOBBING]

13:24.130 --> 13:26.098
[MOUTHING WORDS]

13:26.130 --> 13:28.064
[SOBBING CONTINUES]

13:28.100 --> 13:29.590
[MOUTHING WORDS]

13:29.640 --> 13:32.973
[WEEPING]

13:35.440 --> 13:37.203
[MOUTHING WORDS]

13:45.120 --> 13:48.112
[SOBBING]

13:54.030 --> 13:56.055
[WHIMPERING]

14:00.440 --> 14:02.089
THIS PULLS OUT
INTO A BED,

14:02.140 --> 14:03.061
BUT THAT'S ALL I GOT.

14:03.110 --> 14:04.407
AH, NO WORRIES.

14:04.440 --> 14:07.102
WHAT'S A LITTLE SPOONING
BETWEEN OLD PALS, HUH, GUS?

14:07.140 --> 14:08.971
WELL, GOOD NIGHT.

14:09.010 --> 14:10.272
GOOD NIGHT, ROB.

14:10.310 --> 14:11.868
YOU GOT THE FLOOR.

14:11.910 --> 14:13.639
WE'LL MAKE IT WORK.

14:13.680 --> 14:17.184
YOU DON'T MIND IF I NUDE UP
FOR THE SLEEPOVER, RIGHT?

14:17.220 --> 14:18.380
SERIOUSLY, SHAWN.

14:19.320 --> 14:21.311
THE OTHER ONE IS ON WATCH.

14:21.360 --> 14:22.452
OH, NO, WE'LL BOTH SLEEP.

14:22.490 --> 14:24.026
I'LL PUT ON SOME SOCKS,
MAKE YOU FEEL MORE COMFORTABLE.

14:24.060 --> 14:26.153
STOP PLAYING, SHAWN.

14:26.190 --> 14:28.988
WE'RE HERE
TO SOLVE A CASE.

14:29.030 --> 14:30.497
I ALREADY SOLVED IT.

14:30.530 --> 14:31.462
WHEN?

14:31.500 --> 14:33.331
WHEN YOU WERE FLAPPING THE BOOK
LIKE A BIRD?

14:33.370 --> 14:36.498
GUS, IF YOU MUST KNOW,
IT WAS A BALD EAGLE...

14:36.540 --> 14:38.531
AND YES.

14:40.210 --> 14:41.234
YOU FOUND THE GHOST?

14:41.280 --> 14:42.679
THERE'S NO SUCH THING
AS GHOSTS.

14:42.710 --> 14:44.075
YES, THERE IS, SHAWN.

14:44.110 --> 14:45.543
NO, THERE ISN'T,

14:45.580 --> 14:47.218
BUT THERE IS SUCH A THING
AS A PISSED-OFF EX-GIRLFRIEND.

14:47.250 --> 14:48.512
WHAT EX-GIRLFRIEN D?

14:48.550 --> 14:50.518
NO ONE MENTIONED ANYTHING
ABOUT AN EX.

14:50.550 --> 14:52.040
YOU DIDN'T LOOK
AT THE PHOTO ALBUM?

14:54.090 --> 14:54.909
REDHEAD.

14:54.960 --> 14:56.109
SHE'S CUTE.

14:56.160 --> 14:57.980
WHAT MAKES YOU THINK
SHE'S AN EX?

14:58.030 --> 14:59.054
OH, COME ON.

14:59.090 --> 15:00.125
THERE'S DIRTY DISHES EVERYWHERE.

15:00.160 --> 15:01.457
HIS BEDROOM IS A MESS.

15:01.500 --> 15:02.967
HIS NAILS ARE FILTHY.

15:03.000 --> 15:04.319
HIS HAIR IS HORRIBLE.

15:04.370 --> 15:06.292
NO GIRLFRIEND'S GOING TO PUT UP
WITH THAT.

15:06.330 --> 15:07.467
AND EXHIBIT "A"--

15:07.500 --> 15:09.468
WHO ELSE WOULD
"X" THROUGH HIS FACE

15:09.500 --> 15:11.968
IN ALL OF THESE
PICTURES?

15:12.010 --> 15:12.977
OKAY, OKAY.

15:13.010 --> 15:15.228
SAY SHE'S THE EX.

15:15.280 --> 15:17.202
WE STILL DON'T KNOW
SHE'S ACTUALLY BEEN HERE.

15:17.250 --> 15:20.413
THERE ARE STRANDS OF RED HAIR
ALL OVER THE STUDIO.

15:25.350 --> 15:27.113
SHOULD WE TELL ROBERT?

15:27.160 --> 15:28.457
HOW PSYCHIC WOULD THAT BE?

15:28.490 --> 15:30.082
NO. WE'LL SPEND THE NIGHT.

15:30.130 --> 15:31.085
IT'S FINE.

15:31.130 --> 15:31.824
CATCH UP
WITH THE EX TOMORROW,

15:31.860 --> 15:33.418
TALK TO HER,
SEE WHAT'S GOING ON.

15:33.460 --> 15:36.054
MEANWHILE, I'M GOING TO DO
SOME SIT-UPS.

15:36.100 --> 15:37.624
COME HOLD MY FEET.

15:38.670 --> 15:40.535
I'M GOING TO
DO A THOUSAND!

15:45.340 --> 15:48.207
[FIRE CRACKLING]

15:51.180 --> 15:54.013
[COUGHING]

15:57.150 --> 15:58.583
SHAWN! GET UP!

15:58.620 --> 16:00.053
WHAT?

16:00.090 --> 16:01.011
AAH! AAH!

16:03.030 --> 16:05.055
AH! GET-- GET ROBERT!

16:09.760 --> 16:12.297
I COULD'VE DIED.

16:12.330 --> 16:15.436
IF YOU GUYS WEREN'T HERE, I...

16:15.470 --> 16:18.303
WHY IS IT DOING THIS TO ME?

16:18.340 --> 16:20.570
WHY IS IT TRYING TO KILL ME?

16:20.610 --> 16:21.679
OKAY. OKAY.

16:21.710 --> 16:23.439
ROBERT, HEY, HEY, HEY.

16:23.480 --> 16:25.505
HEY. BOBBY.

16:25.550 --> 16:26.744
LOOK AT ME.

16:26.780 --> 16:30.238
NOW, WHO HERE
HAS COMMUNICATED

16:30.290 --> 16:31.518
WITH MORE
DISPOSSESSED SOULS?

16:31.550 --> 16:32.642
YOU OR ME?

16:32.690 --> 16:34.658
YOU?
THAT'S CORRECT.

16:34.690 --> 16:37.329
NOW I AM TELLING YOU
THAT THIS, THIS FIRE,

16:37.360 --> 16:38.588
WAS NOT AN A'I'I'EMPT
ON YOUR LIFE.

16:38.630 --> 16:39.619
IT WASN'T?

16:39.660 --> 16:40.797
NO.

16:40.830 --> 16:43.526
THIS WAS A SAD AND DESPERATE
CRY FOR HELP

16:43.570 --> 16:45.663
FROM A VERY FRIGHTENED,
VERY LONELY APPARITION.

16:45.700 --> 16:48.089
ARE YOU SURE ABOUT THIS?

16:48.140 --> 16:49.198
ABSOLUTELY.

16:49.240 --> 16:50.798
OF COURSE,
IT'S ALSO POSSIBLE

16:50.840 --> 16:53.479
THAT SOMEONE SIMPLY
LEFI' A CANDLE BURNING.

16:53.510 --> 16:55.171
I DON'T BURN
CANDLES.

16:55.210 --> 16:56.575
GUS, DID YOU
BURN A CANDLE?

16:56.610 --> 16:57.747
WHY WOULD I DO THAT?

16:57.780 --> 16:59.304
CRY FOR HELP IT IS.

16:59.350 --> 17:01.614
NO ONE CAME IN
WHILE WE WERE SLEEPING.

17:01.650 --> 17:03.288
I CHECKED THE DOORS
AND THE WINDOWS.

17:03.320 --> 17:04.639
THEY WERE ALL LOCKED...

17:04.690 --> 17:05.645
FROM THE INSIDE.

17:12.390 --> 17:14.358
WHY ARE YOU
LOOKING AT ME LIKE THAT?

17:14.400 --> 17:15.549
THAT'S ALL YOU DID?

17:15.600 --> 17:16.658
CHECK THE DOORS AND THE WINDOWS?

17:16.700 --> 17:17.621
YEAH. WHY?

17:29.680 --> 17:30.749
WHERE DID THAT
COME FROM?

17:30.780 --> 17:31.804
DON'T LOOK AT ME.

17:31.850 --> 17:33.215
I'M NOT WEARING
LIPSTICK.

17:35.280 --> 17:37.612
THIS IS THE ONLY
POST OFFICE BOX

17:37.650 --> 17:39.140
LISTED FOR REGINA KANE.

17:39.190 --> 17:40.214
ACCORDING TO
DR. BLINN'S CALENDAR,

17:40.260 --> 17:41.386
SHE WAS HIS LAST
APPOINTMENT.

17:41.420 --> 17:42.557
SHE MIGHT HAVE
SEEN SOMETHING.

17:42.590 --> 17:43.784
I WANT TO FIND HER.

17:43.830 --> 17:45.320
WELL, IF THIS IS WHERE
SHE PICKS UP HER MAIL,

17:45.360 --> 17:46.588
SHE PROBABLY LIVES
CLOSE BY.

17:46.630 --> 17:47.528
CANVASS
THE NEIGHBORHOOD.

17:47.560 --> 17:48.527
SEE IF
ANYONE KNOWS HER.

17:48.560 --> 17:49.822
THAT'S A REALLY
SMART APPROACH.

17:49.860 --> 17:52.260
WHAT? THAT--
THAT SHOCKS YOU?

17:52.300 --> 17:53.597
I MEANT THAT AS A COMPLIMENT.

17:53.640 --> 17:54.595
REALLY?

17:54.640 --> 17:55.629
YEAH.

17:55.670 --> 17:57.638
WELL, THANKS A LOT.

17:57.670 --> 17:59.535
WAS THAT SARCASTIC?

17:59.570 --> 18:01.470
NO.

18:01.510 --> 18:03.307
OH. OKAY.

18:03.350 --> 18:05.272
YOU'RE WELCOME.

18:06.880 --> 18:08.541
YOU STILL THINK
IT'S THE EX-GIRLFRIEND?

18:08.580 --> 18:11.413
A WOMAN SCORNED
IS A WOMAN WITH MOTIVE.

18:11.450 --> 18:12.747
WE NEED TO TALK
TO THIS WOMAN.

18:12.790 --> 18:14.712
YOU'RE ON YOUR OWN.

18:14.760 --> 18:16.580
I'M TIED UP WITH WORK
FOR THE REST OF THE WEEK.

18:16.620 --> 18:18.383
GUS, THAT'S SO LAME.

18:18.430 --> 18:20.694
OOH! PULL OVER.

18:22.160 --> 18:24.697
GOOD MORNING, DETECT IVES!

18:24.730 --> 18:26.664
COLLECTING DONATIONS
FOR THE POLICEMAN'S BALL?

18:26.700 --> 18:28.292
WE DON'T HAVE BALLS.

18:30.410 --> 18:31.468
I HON ESTLY HAVE

18:31.510 --> 18:32.169
NO RESPONSE TO THAT.

18:32.210 --> 18:34.269
NEED I REMIND YOU, MR. SPENCER,

18:34.310 --> 18:36.369
WHAT HAPPENS WHEN YOU INTERFERE
WITH A POLICE INVESTIGATION?

18:36.410 --> 18:38.344
UH... THE CASE
GETS SOLVED?

18:38.380 --> 18:39.449
WAIT A MINUTE!

18:39.480 --> 18:40.617
YOU GUYS ARE
WORKING ON

18:40.650 --> 18:41.878
THAT MURDER THINGY,
RIGHT?

18:41.920 --> 18:43.842
I COMPLETELY
FORGOT ABOUT THAT.

18:43.890 --> 18:45.585
HOW'S THAT GOING?

18:48.460 --> 18:49.779
SILLY QUESTION.

18:49.820 --> 18:51.879
WE'LL LET YOU GET BACK
TO YOUR INVESTIGATING.

18:51.930 --> 18:54.728
BYE, JULIET.

18:54.760 --> 18:56.193
OKAY, WHERE TO NEXT?

18:56.230 --> 18:57.663
LISTEN, WE CHANGE
OUR CLOTHES,

18:57.700 --> 18:58.724
WE GET SOME LUNCH,

18:58.770 --> 19:00.192
AND I HAVE TO
GET BACK TO WORK.

19:00.240 --> 19:01.593
GUS, THE PLOT
IS THICKENING.

19:01.640 --> 19:02.891
SHAWN, I'VE ALREADY MISSED
TWO DAYS THIS WEEK.

19:02.940 --> 19:04.635
OH, FINE, FINE, FINE.

19:04.670 --> 19:05.898
YOUR WISHES.
THANK YOU.

19:05.940 --> 19:07.635
YOU KNOW THAT'S RIGHT.

19:11.450 --> 19:12.599
[YAWNING]: OH, BOY.

19:12.650 --> 19:14.641
THERE HE IS!

19:14.680 --> 19:15.874
WHAT TIME IS IT?

19:15.920 --> 19:17.319
DAYTIM E.

19:18.890 --> 19:21.381
WHAT HAPPENED?

19:21.420 --> 19:23.684
I MIGHT HAVE DROPPED
SIX ALLERGY PILLS

19:23.730 --> 19:25.186
IN YOUR FROSTY
WHILE YOU WERE PEEING.

19:25.230 --> 19:26.356
YOU DID WHAT?

19:26.390 --> 19:27.391
WHERE ARE WE?

19:27.430 --> 19:28.522
PALO ALTO.

19:28.560 --> 19:29.527
SAN FRANCISCO?

19:29.560 --> 19:31.289
NO, BUT CLOSE.

19:31.330 --> 19:32.729
ROBERT'S EX-GIRLFRIEND
LIVES UP HERE, GUS,

19:32.770 --> 19:34.465
AND WE REALLY NEED TO
TALK TO HER.

19:34.500 --> 19:35.432
I WILL KILL YOU,
SHAWN...

19:35.470 --> 19:36.732
AND THEN YOU'RE GOING TO
BUY ME SOME NEW TIRES.

19:36.770 --> 19:37.907
OH, COME ON, THIS IS FUN.

19:37.940 --> 19:39.202
ROAD TRIP.

19:39.240 --> 19:40.309
KIDNAPPING.

19:40.340 --> 19:42.308
THAT'S EXACTLY WHAT THIS IS.

19:42.340 --> 19:45.468
THAT'S IT,
WE'RE NOT TALKING.

19:49.620 --> 19:50.848
WHAT, SERIOUSLY?

19:58.260 --> 20:00.455
SO, WE'RE REALLY NOT
TALKING NOW?

20:00.500 --> 20:01.626
COME ON,
HOW MATURE IS THIS?

20:01.660 --> 20:02.558
THE SILENT TREATMENT

20:02.600 --> 20:04.625
IS NOT HOW CONFLICT
GETS RESOLVED, GUS.

20:04.670 --> 20:05.694
WE NEED TO
WORK THROUGH THIS.

20:05.730 --> 20:07.595
WE NEED TO SHARE
OUR FEELINGS...

20:07.640 --> 20:09.562
MAYBE A SMOOTHIE.

20:10.810 --> 20:12.664
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

20:14.810 --> 20:16.368
YES?

20:16.410 --> 20:17.445
NEVER MIND.

20:17.480 --> 20:18.606
IT'S NOT HER.

20:20.580 --> 20:22.514
PARDON ME.

20:29.690 --> 20:31.555
[CELL PHONE CHIRPS AND BUZZES]

20:33.860 --> 20:36.693
WHAT DO I MEAN,
IT'S NOT HER?

20:37.600 --> 20:39.397
LIPS.

20:39.430 --> 20:40.658
LIPS DON'T MATCH.

20:40.700 --> 20:43.635
LIPS THAT KISSED YOUR FOREHEAD
DO NOT BELONG TO AMY KESSLER,

20:43.670 --> 20:44.739
THEREFORE SHE'S NOT OUR GHOST.

20:49.940 --> 20:51.578
YOU DIDN'T DRIVE

20:51.610 --> 20:52.702
ALL THE WAY OUT HERE

20:52.750 --> 20:54.342
SO YOU COULD SAY,
"IT'S NOT HER,"

20:54.380 --> 20:55.369
AND LEAVE?

20:55.420 --> 20:56.717
"WE'RE TALKING TO HEP."

20:59.620 --> 21:01.383
"HER."

21:07.360 --> 21:08.588
"CARLTON...

21:08.630 --> 21:12.566
SEPARATION MEANS APART."

21:12.600 --> 21:13.567
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACH]

21:13.600 --> 21:15.830
WHATCHA GOT THERE?

21:15.870 --> 21:16.996
NOTHING.

21:17.040 --> 21:18.462
ARE YOU OKAY?

21:18.510 --> 21:19.602
OF COURSE I'M OKAY.

21:19.640 --> 21:20.572
YOU LOOK SAD.

21:20.610 --> 21:22.578
I AM SAD.

21:22.610 --> 21:23.577
WHY ARE YOU SAD?

21:23.610 --> 21:24.907
I'M SAD

21:24.950 --> 21:26.645
BECAUSE I DON'T HAVE
MY FORENSICS REPORT

21:26.680 --> 21:27.749
ON MY DEAD DOCTOR,

21:27.780 --> 21:29.372
OR A LEAD

21:29.420 --> 21:30.739
ON MY POSSIBLE WITNESS,
REGINA KANE.

21:30.790 --> 21:31.688
WHAT ABOUT THAT PSYCHIC GUY?

21:31.720 --> 21:33.654
ISN'T SHAWN GREAT
AT THIS SORT OF THING?

21:33.690 --> 21:34.657
FINDING PEOPLE?

21:34.690 --> 21:35.759
MAYBE WE SHOULD BRING HIM IN--

21:35.790 --> 21:37.929
MAYBE YOU SHOULD JUST
KEEP YOUR IDEAS TO YOURSELF.

21:38.930 --> 21:40.795
THAT'S A JOKE, RIGHT?

21:40.830 --> 21:43.663
YES.

21:43.700 --> 21:45.361
YES, IT IS.

21:45.400 --> 21:46.765
OKAY.

21:52.510 --> 21:53.772
VERY NICE.

21:53.810 --> 21:56.973
EXQUISITE BRUSH STROKES.

21:57.010 --> 21:58.705
IT'S A PRINT.

21:58.750 --> 22:00.547
I'M REFERRING, OF COURSE,
TO THE ORIGINAL.

22:00.580 --> 22:02.343
I'M SORRY...

22:02.380 --> 22:03.642
WHAT'S THE NAME OF YOUR GALLERY
AGAIN?

22:03.690 --> 22:06.386
THAT'S BEEN A BIT OF A PROBLEM,
ACTUALLY.

22:06.420 --> 22:07.819
WE WANTED TO CALL IT...

22:07.860 --> 22:09.680
[FEIGNING FRENCH ACCENT]:
LE PETIT LOUVRE...

22:09.720 --> 22:11.426
[NORMAL VOICE]:
BUT APPARENTLY,

22:11.460 --> 22:12.882
THE ART SNOBS IN FRANCE

22:12.930 --> 22:15.922
THINK THEY HAVE A MONOPOLY
ON ALL THINGS LOUVRE.

22:15.960 --> 22:18.929
WE ALSO TRIED
LOUVRE II...

22:18.970 --> 22:21.359
LOUVRE JUNIOR...

22:21.400 --> 22:23.539
NIGHT GALLERY.

22:23.570 --> 22:24.662
NOTHING CLEARED.

22:24.710 --> 22:25.108
THE IMPORTANT
THING IS,

22:25.140 --> 22:26.437
WE WANT TO SHOW

22:26.470 --> 22:28.631
THE AMAZING WORK
OF ROBERT DUNN,

22:28.680 --> 22:30.443
AND HE LISTED YOU
AS A CHARACTER REFERENCE.

22:30.480 --> 22:31.572
WE ARE VERY SELECT

22:31.610 --> 22:33.544
WITH THE CLIENTS
THAT WE TAKE ON.

22:33.580 --> 22:35.138
ISN'T THAT RIGHT, FRANCOIS?

22:35.180 --> 22:36.442
I HAVE TO ADMIT,

22:36.480 --> 22:37.640
I'M SURPRISED ROBERT
WOULD LIST ME

22:37.690 --> 22:38.918
AS A CHARACTER
REFERENCE.

22:38.950 --> 22:40.884
WE DATED FOR A PERIOD,
AND IT DIDN'T END WELL.

22:40.920 --> 22:42.717
CAN I ASK WHY?

22:42.760 --> 22:43.784
NOT TO PRY,

22:43.830 --> 22:45.650
BUT HE DID LIST YOU
AS A REFERENCE.

22:45.690 --> 22:46.679
THE USUAL.

22:46.730 --> 22:48.459
FORGE'ITING DATES.
STANDING ME UP.

22:48.500 --> 22:50.024
SOMETIMES HE'D GET
SO WRAPPED UP IN HIS WORK

22:50.060 --> 22:51.527
HE'D DISAPPEAR
FOR DAYS AT A TIME.

22:51.570 --> 22:52.662
THE WORST WAS WHEN
HE CHEATED ON ME

22:52.700 --> 22:53.667
AND LIED ABOUT IT.

22:53.700 --> 22:55.395
OH...

22:55.440 --> 22:56.862
YOU MUST HAVE BEEN
BURNING WITH FURIOUS ANGER.

22:56.900 --> 22:58.731
IT WAS JUST
SO STUPID.

22:58.770 --> 23:00.032
A GIRLFRIEND OF MINE

23:00.070 --> 23:01.105
SAW HIM IN A CLUB
WITH ANOTHER WOMAN.

23:01.140 --> 23:02.607
HE WAS DRUNK

23:02.640 --> 23:03.777
AND PRETENDED
THAT SHE HAD HIM CONFUSED

23:03.810 --> 23:05.072
WITH SOMEONE ELSE.

23:05.110 --> 23:07.419
HE SAID HIS NAME WAS--
GET THIS-- MARTIN BRODY.

23:07.450 --> 23:09.714
MARTIN BRODY?

23:09.750 --> 23:11.684
ROY SCHEIDER'S CHARACTER
FROM JAWS?

23:11.720 --> 23:13.608
YES. HOW'D YOU KNOW?

23:13.660 --> 23:15.787
WELL, I'VE SEEN JAWS.

23:15.820 --> 23:17.526
IT'S HIS FAVORITE
MOVIE.

23:17.560 --> 23:18.549
ANYWAY, WHEN I ASKED HIM
ABOUT IT,

23:18.590 --> 23:20.023
HE PRETENDED HE'D NEVER EVEN
HEARD OF THE CLUB.

23:20.060 --> 23:21.596
THAT'S, UH...

23:21.630 --> 23:23.188
[FEIGNING FRENCH ACCENT]:
HORRIBLE.

23:23.230 --> 23:26.688
YOU MUST HAVE
WANTED TO KILL HIM.

23:26.730 --> 23:27.594
BUT...

23:27.640 --> 23:29.767
PROBABLY NOT SO MUCH
ANYMORE.

23:29.800 --> 23:31.665
YOU'RE PRETI'Y
HAPPILY ENGAGED,

23:31.710 --> 23:32.904
AREN'T YOU?

23:32.940 --> 23:34.669
YES.

23:34.710 --> 23:35.972
ISN'T THE RING GREAT?

23:36.010 --> 23:38.672
[CH UCKLES POLITELY]

23:44.620 --> 23:47.748
OKAY, SO SHE'S NOT
OUR GHOST.

23:47.790 --> 23:49.451
EVEN THE LONGEST JOURNEYS

23:49.490 --> 23:50.582
CAN START
WITH A TINY MISSTEP.

23:50.630 --> 23:53.224
OVERALL, IT WAS STILL
A VERY GOOD DAY.

23:53.260 --> 23:55.023
HOW WAS IT
A GOOD DAY?

23:55.060 --> 23:57.153
OH, COME ON, GUS.

23:57.200 --> 23:58.997
FIRST OF ALL, ROAD TRIP.
ALWAYS FUN.

23:59.030 --> 24:00.588
WE GOT SOME
FRESH-BAKED SOURDOUGH.

24:00.640 --> 24:02.164
VERY NICE.

24:02.200 --> 24:04.634
AND THE AGENCY'S SENDING US
A NEW SECRETARY TOMORROW.

24:04.670 --> 24:06.160
AND YES,
SHE SPEAKS ENGLISH,

24:06.210 --> 24:07.234
FLUENTLY.

24:07.270 --> 24:08.237
SHAWN, WE TALKED ABOUT THIS.

24:08.280 --> 24:09.633
WE CAN'T AFFORD A RECEPTIONIST.

24:09.680 --> 24:11.773
I DON'T THINK WE CAN AFFORD
NOT TO HAVE ONE.

24:11.810 --> 24:13.141
[TIRES SQUEALING]

24:13.180 --> 24:14.738
GUS?
WHAT?

24:14.780 --> 24:17.112
I THINK MAYBE WE SHOULD MOVE.

24:17.150 --> 24:18.788
COME ON, GUS!
GET IN GEAR!

24:18.820 --> 24:19.912
GO, GO, GO!

24:22.160 --> 24:23.957
[CRASHING]

24:23.990 --> 24:25.628
[HISSING]

24:27.660 --> 24:29.059
HEY!

24:34.040 --> 24:36.133
THE GUY'S
LIKE A WHIPPET.

24:36.170 --> 24:37.660
TELL ME ABOUT IT.

24:37.710 --> 24:39.234
WHAT'S THE SUPERSMELLER SAY?

24:39.270 --> 24:41.909
SOMEBODY HAD
TOO MUCH TO DRINK.

24:45.250 --> 24:47.514
[CHUCKLING]

24:47.550 --> 24:48.676
[CLAPPING]

24:48.720 --> 24:49.778
WHAT ARE YOU SO HAPPY FOR?

24:49.820 --> 24:51.219
WE ALMOST GOT KILLED.

24:51.250 --> 24:52.786
THIS WAS NOT AN ACCIDENT.

24:52.820 --> 24:54.185
WHOEVER THAT IS
WAS WAITING FOR US,

24:54.220 --> 24:56.552
AND WE HAVE A NEW SUSPECT
FOR ROBERT'S GHOST.

24:59.830 --> 25:02.048
[DOORBELL CHIMING]

25:02.100 --> 25:03.590
HE DIDN'T ANSWER
HIS PHONE.

25:03.630 --> 25:06.121
MAYBE HE'S NOT HOME.

25:06.170 --> 25:07.933
ROBERT?

25:07.970 --> 25:08.994
OR MAYBE...

25:09.040 --> 25:11.565
WHOEVER TRIED TO KILL US
LAST NIGHT

25:11.610 --> 25:13.066
ALSO PAID ROBERT A VISIT...

25:13.110 --> 25:14.236
AND LEFI' THE DOOR UNLOCKED.

25:14.280 --> 25:16.737
ANYBODY HOME?

25:16.780 --> 25:18.600
ROBERT?

25:18.650 --> 25:20.709
BOB?

25:22.020 --> 25:24.181
SHAWN, YOU MIGHT
WANT TO SEE THIS.

25:25.890 --> 25:26.879
"SAVE ME. I'M TRAPPED."

25:26.920 --> 25:28.319
HMM.

25:28.360 --> 25:29.850
I DON'T WANT TO
JUMP TO CONCLUSIONS HERE,

25:29.890 --> 25:31.926
BUT THIS VERY WELL MAY BE
A CRY FOR HELP.

25:31.960 --> 25:33.757
MAYBE SOMEONE DIED HERE...

25:33.800 --> 25:34.949
OR WAS BURIED ALIVE.

25:35.000 --> 25:37.150
THIS COULD BE THE CRY
OF A TORTURED SOUL.

25:37.200 --> 25:38.997
SO THIS GUY
JUST HAPPENS TO MOVE

25:39.030 --> 25:41.590
INTO TWO HAUNTED HOUSES
IN A ROW?

25:41.640 --> 25:43.164
DON'T TOUCH THAT.
IT'S BLOOD.

25:43.200 --> 25:44.303
IT'S NOT BLOOD.

25:44.340 --> 25:46.035
ENJOY YOUR HEPATITIS.

25:46.070 --> 25:47.833
AND THIS TORTURED SOUL

25:47.880 --> 25:49.905
MIGHT BE LESS TORTURED
WITH A LATEX ENAMEL.

25:49.940 --> 25:52.807
HE WOULDN'T GET
THESE MESSY DRIPS.

26:07.730 --> 26:09.721
NOW WHAT?

26:14.170 --> 26:16.866
OOH...

26:16.900 --> 26:18.128
I'VE GOT IT.
I'VE GOT IT.

26:18.170 --> 26:19.660
I'VEGOTIT.

26:19.710 --> 26:21.769
HALLELUJAH!

26:24.950 --> 26:26.975
WOW.

26:27.010 --> 26:28.841
WHAT?

26:31.790 --> 26:34.884
YOU'VE GOT TO SEE THIS.

26:34.920 --> 26:38.128
[GRU NTS]

26:38.160 --> 26:39.957
HUH.

26:39.990 --> 26:41.924
NOT WHAT I WAS EXPECTING.

26:44.930 --> 26:46.966
OKAY, I KNOW WHAT
I'M LOOKING AT, BUT...

26:47.000 --> 26:49.059
WHAT DOES IT MEAN?

26:54.140 --> 26:55.630
IS IT A GHOST?

26:55.680 --> 26:58.843
NO, BUDDY,
IT'S NOT A GHOST.

26:58.880 --> 27:01.041
IS THERE A WOMAN
LIVING UP HERE?

27:01.080 --> 27:03.981
WELL, THAT WOULD
CERTAINLY EXPLAIN

27:04.020 --> 27:05.885
THE PERFUME
ROBERT'S BEEN SMELLING

27:05.920 --> 27:07.387
AND ALL THE RED HAIR
LAYING EVERYWHERE,

27:07.420 --> 27:08.819
BUT NO, NO DICE.

27:08.860 --> 27:09.952
THEN WHAT IS IT?

27:09.990 --> 27:10.957
OH, COME ON, GUS.

27:10.990 --> 27:12.287
LOOK.

27:16.160 --> 27:17.388
WHAT?

27:17.430 --> 27:19.091
ROBERT IS A WOMAN.

27:19.130 --> 27:21.064
NO, HE'S NOT.

27:21.100 --> 27:24.069
NOT ALL THE TIME,
BUT SOMETIMES.

27:24.110 --> 27:25.907
NO, DOESN'T SEEM LIKE THE TYPE.

27:25.940 --> 27:26.907
HE'S NOT THE TYPE.

27:26.940 --> 27:28.032
THEN HOW?

27:28.080 --> 27:31.049
UNLESS HE HAS
THAT PERSONALITY THING.

27:31.080 --> 27:32.240
WHAT PERSONALITY THING?

27:32.280 --> 27:33.713
OH, YOU KNOW
WHAT I'M TALKING ABOUT--

27:33.750 --> 27:35.411
THE MULTIPLE PERSONALITY
DISEASE.

27:35.450 --> 27:37.839
YOU KNOW, THAT...
WHAT'S-HER-NAME HAD.

27:37.890 --> 27:38.948
THE FLYING NUN,

27:38.990 --> 27:40.048
IN THE OTHER THING,
THE TV MOVIE.

27:40.090 --> 27:41.216
SMOKEY AND THE BANDIT?

27:42.320 --> 27:43.287
YEAH, DUDE.

27:43.320 --> 27:44.218
SMOKEY AND THE BANDIT.

27:44.260 --> 27:45.727
YES.

27:45.760 --> 27:46.954
WHAT DOES THAT
HAVE TO DO

27:46.990 --> 27:48.059
WITH MULTIPLE
PERSONALITIES?

27:48.100 --> 27:48.998
I ASKED A REAL QUESTION.

27:49.030 --> 27:49.894
GIVE ME A REAL ANSWER,

27:49.930 --> 27:50.862
NOT A RANDOM GUESS.

27:50.900 --> 27:51.320
OKAY, FINE.

27:51.370 --> 27:52.689
HOOPER.

27:52.730 --> 27:54.869
HOOPER?
HOOPER.

27:54.900 --> 27:55.889
HOOPER WAS A STUNT MAN.

27:55.940 --> 27:56.998
OH.

27:57.040 --> 27:58.962
I DON'T THINK
SALLY FIELD WAS EVEN IN HOOPER.

27:59.010 --> 28:00.739
WHO ARE YOU THINKING OF?

28:00.780 --> 28:01.769
TERRY BRADSHAW.

28:01.810 --> 28:03.004
YES.

28:03.040 --> 28:04.905
IS IT NORMA RAE?

28:04.950 --> 28:06.906
NO, BUT THAT WOULD HAVE
MADE THAT MOVIE A LOT COOLER.

28:06.950 --> 28:08.941
THE THING YOU'RE ASKING ABOUT,
SHAWN,

28:08.980 --> 28:11.448
IS REFERRED TO AS
DISSOCIATIVE IDENTITY DISORDER.

28:11.490 --> 28:12.787
THAT'S IT!

28:12.820 --> 28:13.855
THAT'S WHAT ROBERT HAS, GUS.

28:13.890 --> 28:15.016
IT ALL MAKES SENSE.

28:15.060 --> 28:15.913
DO YOU KNOW HOW RARE THAT IS?

28:15.960 --> 28:17.154
I'M NOT SAYING
ALL OF SANTA BARBARA HAS IT.

28:17.190 --> 28:18.919
JUST ROBERT, ONE GUY.

28:18.960 --> 28:20.359
I THINK THAT QUALIFIES
AS PRETI'Y RARE.

28:20.390 --> 28:21.823
I DON'T KNOW, SHAWN.

28:21.860 --> 28:23.191
THESE ARE HUGE.

28:23.230 --> 28:25.061
LOOK. THINK ABOUT IT.

28:25.100 --> 28:27.125
TWO SEPARATE
BUT DISTINCT PERSONALITIES,

28:27.170 --> 28:28.762
ONE BODY.

28:28.800 --> 28:30.802
ONE'S A MAN,
THE OTHER'S A WOMAN.

28:30.840 --> 28:33.400
THE FEMALE PERSONALITY
COOKS DINNER.

28:33.440 --> 28:34.976
ROBERT THINKS THE MEALS
ARE THE WORK OF A GHOST.

28:36.380 --> 28:38.803
THE FEMALE REARRANGES
THE FURNITURE.

28:38.850 --> 28:39.805
ROBERT THINKS, UH,

28:39.850 --> 28:42.148
THE GHOST IS MOVING THINGS
WHEN HE'S NOT AROUND.

28:42.180 --> 28:43.477
HIS OLD GIRLFRIEND DID SAY

28:43.520 --> 28:44.987
THAT HE WOULD DISAPPEAR
FOR STRETCHES AT A TIME,

28:45.020 --> 28:46.248
WHICH WOULD EXPLAIN.

28:46.290 --> 28:47.985
WHEN THE FEMALE PERSONALITY
WAS IN CONTROL,

28:48.020 --> 28:49.510
ROBERT
WOULD DISAPPEAR.

28:49.560 --> 28:53.280
AND HE WOULD HAVE NO CLUE
ABOUT ANY OF IT.

28:53.330 --> 28:54.991
NOW, ALL WE NEED
TO FIGURE OUT

28:55.030 --> 28:57.396
IS HOW TO BRING OUT THE WOMAN
SO THAT WE CAN TALK TO HER.

28:57.430 --> 28:58.988
OKAY.

28:59.030 --> 29:01.134
OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.

29:02.470 --> 29:05.007
TRIGGERS.

29:05.040 --> 29:06.132
SHOOT HIM? THEN WHAT?

29:06.170 --> 29:07.102
NO, NO.

29:07.140 --> 29:09.005
SIGHTS, SOUNDS, SMELLS.

29:09.040 --> 29:11.508
SOMETHING THAT WOULD TRIGGER
THE PERSONALITY TO COME OUT.

29:11.550 --> 29:13.074
TRIGGERS IT IS.

29:13.110 --> 29:13.917
GUS, THIS IS...

29:13.950 --> 29:15.417
THIS IS GOING TO BE
KIND OF COOL.

29:15.450 --> 29:17.315
OR WEIRD.

29:20.250 --> 29:22.787
WHERE DID ALL THIS STUFF
COME FROM?

29:24.030 --> 29:27.386
IS THIS
WHERE SHE LIVES?

29:27.430 --> 29:28.954
THE... THE...

29:29.000 --> 29:31.093
THE ANGRY FEMALE SPIRIT
THAT YOU SENSED?

29:31.130 --> 29:33.121
OH... YES.

29:33.170 --> 29:36.936
I FEEL HER
VERY STRONGLY HERE, ROBERT.

29:36.970 --> 29:39.268
DO YOU?

29:39.310 --> 29:42.302
DO YOU FEEL...

29:43.950 --> 29:45.076
PRETI'Y?

29:46.410 --> 29:47.946
WHAT?

29:47.980 --> 29:50.847
DO YOU FEEL PRETI'Y?

29:50.890 --> 29:53.211
HE... HE MEANS,

29:53.250 --> 29:56.856
DO YOU FEEL
A FEMALE PRESENCE?

29:58.130 --> 30:01.224
UH, NO, BUT I'M NOT PSYCHIC.

30:01.260 --> 30:02.989
DO YOU THINK

30:03.030 --> 30:04.122
THAT YOU CAN, UH--

30:05.970 --> 30:07.119
[COUGHING]

30:08.200 --> 30:09.861
COMMUNICATE WITH HER?

30:09.900 --> 30:10.867
I'M TRYING.

30:10.910 --> 30:11.865
IAM.

30:11.910 --> 30:13.969
UH...

30:14.010 --> 30:15.875
I'M SORRY.

30:15.910 --> 30:17.571
OKAY.

30:17.610 --> 30:19.077
YOU GUYS ARE STARTING
TO CREEP ME OUT,

30:19.110 --> 30:21.169
SO IF I'M NOT NEEDED,

30:21.220 --> 30:22.573
I THINK I'LL GO
BACK DOWNSTAIRS.

30:22.620 --> 30:23.609
OKAY.

30:23.650 --> 30:25.015
LET ME JUST
PUT THIS AWAY.

30:25.050 --> 30:27.518
WE'LL ALL GO DOWN
TOGETHER.

30:33.190 --> 30:34.919
YOU COMING, SHAWN?

30:34.960 --> 30:37.099
YES.

30:37.130 --> 30:40.019
OH...
WOW, ROBERT.

30:41.070 --> 30:42.867
THESE ARE SOME
TERRIFIC CLOTH ES.

30:42.900 --> 30:46.165
I BET THEY LOOK
ABSOLUTELY BEAUTIFUL ON YOU...

30:46.210 --> 30:47.837
REGINA.

30:49.140 --> 30:50.368
REGINA? WHO--

30:50.410 --> 30:52.002
WHO ARE YOU TALKING TO?

30:52.050 --> 30:54.018
YES. YES, GUS.

30:54.050 --> 30:55.347
WHY DON'T YOU TELL...

30:55.380 --> 30:57.917
REGINA...

30:57.950 --> 31:02.080
HOW MUCH
YOU LIKE HER NICE CLOTHES?

31:04.430 --> 31:06.386
WOW.

31:06.430 --> 31:09.524
YEAH, REGINA.

31:09.560 --> 31:12.063
[WHISPERING]: REGINA.

31:12.100 --> 31:13.499
YOU LOOK BEAUTIFUL.

31:24.680 --> 31:26.944
[EFFEMINATELY]:
THANK YOU, GUS.

31:29.050 --> 31:33.419
I CAN'T TELL YOU HOW GLAD I AM

31:33.450 --> 31:37.056
THAT YOU GOT MY MESSAGE.

31:37.090 --> 31:38.079
SO...

31:38.130 --> 31:41.588
DO YOU THINK
THAT YOU CAN HELP ME?

31:42.700 --> 31:45.498
PLEASE?

31:46.500 --> 31:48.229
DUDE.

31:51.170 --> 31:53.309
THIS ISN'T RIGHT.

31:58.650 --> 32:00.971
I MUST LOOK HORRIBLE.

32:01.020 --> 32:02.942
NO, NOT AT ALL.

32:02.980 --> 32:04.288
YOU ARE TOO KIND,

32:04.320 --> 32:05.309
BUT, THEN AGAIN,

32:05.350 --> 32:06.510
I ALREADY KNEW THAT.

32:06.550 --> 32:08.211
THE WAY YOU COMFORTED ROBERT...

32:08.260 --> 32:10.353
YOU WERE SO SWEET...

32:12.530 --> 32:14.020
UNLIKE MOST MEN.

32:14.060 --> 32:16.324
AFRAID TO SHOW THEIR EMOTIONS.

32:16.360 --> 32:17.964
WELL, I...

32:18.000 --> 32:19.160
I'VE BEEN HURT A LOT.

32:19.200 --> 32:20.269
NOW, IF YOU TWO
DON'T MIND,

32:20.300 --> 32:21.289
I REALLY MUST

32:21.340 --> 32:23.160
PUT ON MY FACE.

32:26.440 --> 32:28.135
WOW.

32:28.180 --> 32:29.704
SO, REGINA,

32:29.740 --> 32:30.968
THIS MESSAGE
ON THE WALL,

32:31.010 --> 32:32.102
THIS WAS YOUR WAY

32:32.150 --> 32:33.674
OF TRYING TO GET
ROBERT'S ATTENTION?

32:33.710 --> 32:35.575
WELL, HE DOESN'T EVEN KNOW
I'M ALIVE.

32:35.620 --> 32:37.019
WHY NOT WRITE HIM
A LETTER,

32:37.050 --> 32:38.142
OR AN E-MAIL,

32:38.190 --> 32:40.112
OR EVEN A POST-IT,
EVEN?

32:40.150 --> 32:41.310
I TRIED.

32:41.360 --> 32:42.349
I REALLY DID TRY.

32:42.390 --> 32:44.426
BUT EVERY TIME,
SOMETHING OR SOMEONE

32:44.460 --> 32:46.189
STOPPED YOU.

32:46.230 --> 32:47.026
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

32:47.060 --> 32:48.596
I THINK
THERE'S ANOTHER PERSONALITY.

32:48.630 --> 32:49.654
REGINA, THERE'S ANOTHER

32:49.700 --> 32:51.395
PERSONALITY,
ISN'T THERE?

32:51.430 --> 32:52.499
I MEAN, YOU DON'T
SMASH PICTURES

32:52.530 --> 32:54.031
OR START FIRES.

32:54.070 --> 32:55.230
YOU WOULD NEVER
STRANGLE ROBERT.

32:55.270 --> 32:56.191
NO, I WOULDN'T.

32:56.240 --> 32:57.593
REGINA,

32:57.640 --> 33:00.006
THE POLICE WOULD LIKE
TO SPEAK WITH YOU.

33:00.040 --> 33:01.576
THEY'RE INVESTIGATING
DR. BLINN'S MURDER.

33:01.610 --> 33:03.100
THEY THINK YOU MIGHT HAVE
SEEN SOMETHING.

33:03.140 --> 33:04.368
YOU COULD BE
IN DANGER.

33:04.410 --> 33:06.275
I DIDN'T SEE ANYTHING.

33:06.310 --> 33:08.278
I DIDN'T EVEN GO
TO MY APPOINTMENT.

33:08.320 --> 33:10.618
WHY WOULD ANYONE
WANT TO HURT DR. BLINN?

33:10.650 --> 33:12.208
HE WAS
SUCH A NICE MAN,

33:12.250 --> 33:15.151
AND HE WAS DOING SO MUCH
TO HELP ME.

33:19.230 --> 33:22.722
WELL, YOU OUGHT TO KNOW BETTER
THAN TO ASK THAT.

33:22.760 --> 33:24.318
THAT'S BETWEEN A WOMAN
AND HER DOCTOR.

33:25.630 --> 33:27.166
[QUIETLY]: OKAY.

33:27.200 --> 33:28.428
UNLESS YOU'RE GOING TO
ASK HER OUT,

33:28.470 --> 33:29.732
I THINK
WE'RE DONE HERE.

33:29.770 --> 33:31.328
HOW DO WE GET ROBERT BACK?

33:31.370 --> 33:32.462
I HAVE NO IDEA.

33:32.510 --> 33:34.273
WELL, YOU'RE HER
VERY SPECIAL FRIEND.

33:36.480 --> 33:38.368
UM...

33:41.650 --> 33:42.639
REGINA?

33:44.190 --> 33:45.748
WE WOULD LIKE TO
SPEAK WITH ROBERT.

33:45.790 --> 33:49.317
CAN YOU LET ROBERT
COME OUT AND PLAY?

33:49.360 --> 33:52.488
[SNAPS COMPACT CLOSED,
SETS IT DOWN]

33:58.470 --> 34:00.597
FOR YOU?

34:00.630 --> 34:02.495
OF COURSE I CAN.

34:02.540 --> 34:04.303
THANK YOU.

34:04.340 --> 34:05.807
AND I DO HOPE
THAT WE MEET AGAIN.

34:08.210 --> 34:10.201
ROBERT?

34:13.310 --> 34:15.073
ROBERT?

34:16.380 --> 34:18.348
ROBERT?

34:18.390 --> 34:20.187
TRY "BOB."

34:23.290 --> 34:24.552
AAH!

34:24.590 --> 34:25.818
[HYPERVENTILATING]

34:25.860 --> 34:27.623
EASY, EASY,
EASY, EASY, EASY.

34:27.660 --> 34:29.651
WE KNOW
IT SEEMS WEIRD--

34:29.700 --> 34:31.725
AND-- AND--
AND ACTUALLY, IT IS.

34:31.770 --> 34:33.795
IT'S REALLY WEIRD.

34:33.830 --> 34:34.637
BUT WE HAVE GOOD NEWS.

34:35.770 --> 34:37.863
WE FIGURED OUT
WHO YOUR GHOST IS.

34:37.900 --> 34:39.265
WHO?

34:39.310 --> 34:41.335
YOU.

34:41.380 --> 34:42.836
[CHUCKLING AWKWARDLY]

34:42.880 --> 34:45.201
YOU'RE HAUNTING
YOURSELF.

34:49.620 --> 34:50.644
YEP, LIFE IS GOOD.

34:50.680 --> 34:52.341
LIFE IS GREAT.

34:52.390 --> 34:54.756
ROBERT GETS THE HELP
HE SO DESPERATELY NEEDS,

34:54.790 --> 34:56.212
AND WE GET TO MARINATE

34:56.260 --> 34:57.318
IN THE DELICIOUS
SATISFACTION

34:57.360 --> 34:58.679
OF ANOTHER JOB
WELL DONE.

34:58.730 --> 35:00.288
LEADING LASSITER
TO REGINA,

35:00.330 --> 35:02.150
EVEN THOUGH
SHE SAW NOTHING?

35:02.200 --> 35:03.258
THAT'S PROFESSIONAL
COURTESY.

35:03.300 --> 35:05.120
PLUS, IT HELPS
RAISE OUR STOCK, GUS.

35:05.170 --> 35:07.422
OOH! CRIME SCENE PHOTOS!

35:07.470 --> 35:09.791
LOVE CRIME SCENE PHOTOS.

35:11.470 --> 35:12.801
MAY I HELP YOU?

35:12.840 --> 35:15.308
DETECTIVE O'HARA.

35:15.340 --> 35:17.535
WHAT A TRULY
PLEASANT SURPRISE.

35:17.580 --> 35:18.774
MM-HMM.

35:18.810 --> 35:20.243
I JUST DROPPED BY

35:20.280 --> 35:21.918
TO TELL DETECTIVE LASSITER
THAT I HAVE--

35:21.950 --> 35:23.315
WE...
YEAH.

35:23.350 --> 35:24.681
HAVE INFORMATION
REGARDING

35:24.720 --> 35:27.245
THE WHEREABOUTS
OF A ONE REGINA KANE.

35:27.290 --> 35:29.383
HOW DID YOU KNOW ABOUT--

35:29.420 --> 35:32.184
NEVER MIND.

35:32.230 --> 35:33.379
STAY RIGHT HERE. DON'T MOVE.

35:33.430 --> 35:35.159
I'LL GO FIND HIM.

35:36.300 --> 35:37.255
OOH!

35:37.300 --> 35:38.767
SHAWN?

35:38.800 --> 35:40.222
SHAWN, DON'T DO THIS.

35:40.270 --> 35:42.534
[HUMMING]

35:42.570 --> 35:44.834
[GUNSHOTS]

35:54.220 --> 35:55.517
[HUMMING]

36:07.830 --> 36:08.956
OH, GUS, LOOK AT THIS!
LOOK, LOOK, LOOK!

36:09.000 --> 36:09.955
WHAT?

36:10.000 --> 36:10.796
HERE, ON THE FLOOR,

36:10.830 --> 36:12.263
WHERE POOR DR. BLINN'S
BODY WAS LAYING.

36:12.300 --> 36:14.291
A TOOTHPICK.

36:14.340 --> 36:17.229
A CHEWED TOOTHPICK.

36:19.410 --> 36:20.468
YEAH. SO?

36:20.510 --> 36:21.169
DON'T YOU REMEMBER?

36:21.210 --> 36:22.529
THE CAR THAT TRIED TO RAMMED US?

36:22.580 --> 36:23.604
ON THE SEAT?

36:23.640 --> 36:24.709
CH EWED TOOTH PICK.

36:24.750 --> 36:26.308
OH!

36:26.350 --> 36:27.977
OH, THAT MEANS...

36:28.010 --> 36:28.908
THE PERSON THAT KILLED DR. BLINN

36:28.950 --> 36:30.542
IS THE SAME PERSON
THAT TRIED TO KILL US.

36:30.580 --> 36:31.239
IT'S A CH EWED
TOOTHPICK, SHAWN.

36:31.290 --> 36:32.609
LOTS OF PEOPLE CHEW TOOTHPICKS.

36:32.650 --> 36:34.311
YES, BUT WE WERE WORKING
FOR ROBERT.

36:34.360 --> 36:35.452
ROBERT IS ALSO REGINA.

36:35.490 --> 36:36.582
REGINA IS A PATIENT

36:36.620 --> 36:37.609
OF...

36:37.660 --> 36:38.627
DR. BLINN.

36:38.660 --> 36:39.786
YES! TAKE THE BATON!

36:39.830 --> 36:40.956
SO WHOEVER THE KILLER IS

36:40.990 --> 36:43.595
KNEW BOTH ROBERT
AND REGINA.

36:43.630 --> 36:46.565
HE SAID HIS NAME WAS--
GET THIS--

36:46.600 --> 36:47.589
MARTIN BRODY.

36:47.630 --> 36:48.631
HOW DUMB IS THAT?

36:50.870 --> 36:51.837
OH!

36:51.870 --> 36:53.303
MARTIN BRODY.

36:53.340 --> 36:54.898
OF COURSE.

36:54.940 --> 36:56.305
THAT'S ROBERT'S
OTHER PERSONALITY--

36:56.340 --> 36:57.409
THE VIOLENT ONE.

36:57.440 --> 36:58.839
BUT WHY WOULD HE KILL
DR. BLINN?

36:58.880 --> 36:59.949
THAT DEPENDS ENTIRELY

36:59.980 --> 37:02.414
ON WHAT REGINA
WAS SEEING HIM FOR.

37:02.450 --> 37:04.589
OH, YOU'VE GOT TO BE KIDDING ME.

37:04.620 --> 37:05.917
WHAT?

37:05.950 --> 37:08.714
DR. BLINN'S PATIENT FILES.

37:08.760 --> 37:10.819
ALL WE HAVE TO DO
IS FIND REGINA'S.

37:14.630 --> 37:16.257
[COCKS GUN]

37:24.070 --> 37:26.038
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

37:26.070 --> 37:27.469
HMM?

37:27.510 --> 37:28.909
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

37:28.940 --> 37:30.874
SHOOTING.

37:30.910 --> 37:32.377
IT RELAXES ME.

37:32.410 --> 37:33.604
SHAWN SPENCER SAYS

37:33.650 --> 37:34.548
HE HAS INFORMATION
FOR YOU.

37:34.580 --> 37:35.547
WHERE IS HE?

37:35.580 --> 37:37.275
AT YOUR DESK.

37:37.320 --> 37:38.787
IS ANYONE WATCHING HIM?

37:38.820 --> 37:40.788
UH...

37:40.820 --> 37:43.015
FOUND IT.

37:43.060 --> 37:44.015
OH, NO.

37:44.060 --> 37:45.379
WHAT?

37:45.430 --> 37:47.352
GENDER REASSIGNMENT?

37:47.390 --> 37:49.358
OH...

37:49.400 --> 37:50.697
REGINA'S TIRED

37:50.730 --> 37:52.368
OF FEELING LIKE A WOMAN
TRAPPED IN A MAN'S BODY,

37:52.400 --> 37:54.027
SO SHE WANTS TO
HAVE HER PARTS...

37:54.070 --> 37:55.731
OH, MY G--

37:55.770 --> 37:56.998
WAIT A SECOND.

37:57.040 --> 37:59.861
THAT MEANS,
IF REGINA WAS SUCCESSFUL,

37:59.910 --> 38:01.730
BOTH ROBERT
AND THE MARTIN PERSONALITY

38:01.780 --> 38:03.407
WOULD ALSO LOSE THEIR PARTS.

38:03.440 --> 38:04.976
BUT MARTIN CAN'T DO ANYTHING
TO HURT REGINA,

38:05.010 --> 38:06.705
BECAUSE HE'D ONLY BE
HURTING HIMSELF.

38:06.750 --> 38:09.878
SO, DRESSED AS REGINA,
HE GOES AFTER DR. BLINN.

38:09.920 --> 38:10.875
THAT WOULD EXPLAIN
HOW ROBERT

38:10.920 --> 38:11.443
GOT THE MARKS
ON HIS NECK,

38:11.490 --> 38:12.889
AND WITH DR. BLINN DEAD,

38:12.920 --> 38:14.456
ROBERT FIGURED
THAT REGINA

38:14.490 --> 38:15.457
WOULD CHANGE HER MIND

38:15.490 --> 38:16.514
ABOUT THE GENDER
REASSIGNMENT.

38:16.560 --> 38:17.913
RIGHT!

38:17.960 --> 38:19.359
WE GOT THAT!

38:19.390 --> 38:20.789
ONLY SHE HASN'T.

38:24.400 --> 38:26.027
GUS. NO, NO.

38:26.070 --> 38:27.094
SHE FOUND ANOTHER DOCTOR.

38:27.130 --> 38:28.358
SHE'S SEEING HIM. TODAY.

38:28.400 --> 38:30.038
WHEN?

38:30.070 --> 38:31.560
RIGHT NOW.

38:31.610 --> 38:32.702
RIGHT NOW, SHAWN?

38:32.740 --> 38:33.832
LIKE IN 10 MINUTES.

38:33.870 --> 38:35.428
OH. OKAY.

38:39.980 --> 38:41.106
OKAY, NOW.

38:41.150 --> 38:43.778
[WEEPING]

38:43.820 --> 38:44.980
[SOBBING]

38:45.020 --> 38:46.647
THERE HAD BETTER BE

38:46.690 --> 38:48.009
A REALLY GOOD EXPLANATION
FOR THIS.

38:48.050 --> 38:49.950
HE WAS IN SOME SORT OF TRANCE.
I COULDN'T CONTROL HIM.

38:49.990 --> 38:52.049
[WEEPING]

38:52.090 --> 38:54.024
HE SAYS THIS IS THE KILLER.

38:54.060 --> 38:55.095
KILL...

38:55.130 --> 38:57.348
HE'S GOING TO KILL AGAIN.

38:59.100 --> 39:00.567
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.

39:00.600 --> 39:01.862
WHO?
WHO'S HE GOING TO KILL?

39:01.900 --> 39:03.367
WHAT IS IT, SHAWN?

39:03.400 --> 39:04.094
[GASPS]

39:05.440 --> 39:07.704
WATCH OUT,
WATCH OUT!

39:07.740 --> 39:11.198
[BABBLING]

39:15.080 --> 39:17.617
[SOBBING]

39:17.650 --> 39:18.947
DR. DRAKE?

39:18.990 --> 39:20.389
[WHIMPERING]

39:20.420 --> 39:22.854
GENDER REASSIGNMENT?

39:22.890 --> 39:23.914
THAT'S A BIG STEP, REGINA.

39:23.960 --> 39:26.781
WHY DON'T YOU TELL ME
WHY IT'S IMPORTANT TO YOU.

39:26.830 --> 39:27.785
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

39:27.830 --> 39:28.854
IT'S OKAY.

39:28.900 --> 39:30.390
THE MACHINE
CAN GET THAT.

39:30.430 --> 39:31.465
THIS IS YOUR TIME.

39:32.670 --> 39:35.662
THANK YOU, DR. DRAKE.

39:38.910 --> 39:40.798
NO ANSWER.
IT'S JUST THE MACHINE.

39:40.840 --> 39:41.807
WE HAVE TO GO NOW.

39:41.840 --> 39:43.068
IT COULD ALREADY BE TOO LATE.

39:43.110 --> 39:44.031
LET'S GO.

39:46.080 --> 39:47.104
I KNOW THIS CAN BE
A DIFFICULT PROCESS,

39:47.150 --> 39:48.640
BUT IT REALLY IS NECESSARY

39:48.680 --> 39:51.808
TO ENSURE THAT YOU'RE READY
PSYCHOLOGICALLY

39:51.850 --> 39:53.078
FOR A CHANGE LIKE THIS.

39:53.120 --> 39:54.678
YOU DO SEEM LIKE
AN EXCELLENT CANDIDATE

39:54.720 --> 39:56.017
FOR SURGERY.

39:56.060 --> 39:58.153
OUR TIME IS UP.

39:58.190 --> 40:02.126
WHY DON'T WE PICK UP HERE
AGAIN NEXT WEEK, OKAY, REGINA?

40:03.500 --> 40:05.388
OKEY-DOKEY.

40:09.100 --> 40:10.897
ONLY...

40:12.140 --> 40:15.029
MY NAME IS NOT REGINA.

40:15.080 --> 40:16.536
HOLD IT!

40:18.980 --> 40:20.470
GET UP!

40:21.780 --> 40:23.611
WHAT'S GOING ON?

40:23.650 --> 40:25.049
[SHAWN]: ROBERT? BOB?
YOU BACK THERE, BUDDY?

40:25.090 --> 40:26.614
WHAT AM I DOING HERE?

40:36.760 --> 40:38.057
GREAT.

40:38.100 --> 40:39.761
THAN KS.

40:41.100 --> 40:42.237
GOOD NEWS.

40:42.270 --> 40:43.669
THEY'RE GOING TO
ADMIT ROBERT

40:43.700 --> 40:44.803
INTO THE H.T. WINDSOR
FACILITY

40:44.840 --> 40:46.137
IN CHICAGO,

40:46.170 --> 40:48.638
AND HIS DOCTOR THINKS
HIS PROGNOSIS IS GOOD.

40:48.680 --> 40:51.740
DON'T YOU UNDERSTAND, SHAWN?

40:51.780 --> 40:53.668
THAT'S THE PREMIER
MENTAL HEALTH HOSPITAL

40:53.710 --> 40:54.449
IN THE COUNTRY.

40:54.480 --> 40:55.572
YEAH, THAT'S GOOD.
THAT'S AWESOME.

40:55.620 --> 40:57.918
WHO IS THAT?

40:57.950 --> 40:59.144
LESLIE.

40:59.190 --> 41:00.748
OH, NO.
NO, NO, NO, NO.

41:00.790 --> 41:02.212
LESLIE IS SUPPOSED TO BE
A SWIMSUIT MODEL.

41:02.260 --> 41:04.626
UNFORTUNATELY, HE IS,

41:04.660 --> 41:05.729
ALTHOUGH HE SAYS
HE'S GETTING

41:05.760 --> 41:06.749
COMPLETELY SICK
OF THE GRIND.

41:06.790 --> 41:07.825
I HAVE TO CALL THE AGENCY.

41:07.860 --> 41:09.225
THEY'RE COMPLETELY
MISREPRESENTING THEIR CLIENTELE.

41:09.260 --> 41:10.659
LESLIE'S A GUY'S NAME, TOO.

41:10.700 --> 41:12.895
OKAY.

41:12.930 --> 41:14.591
WE HAVE TO FIRE HIM.

41:14.640 --> 41:16.232
FIRE HIM?
ON WHAT GROUNDS?

41:16.270 --> 41:16.929
WHAT GROUNDS?

41:16.970 --> 41:18.699
ON THE GROUNDS THAT HE'S A DUDE.

41:18.740 --> 41:19.729
THAT'S
DISCRIMINATION.

41:19.770 --> 41:20.839
WE CAN'T DO THAT.

41:20.870 --> 41:22.030
OKAY, LISTEN TO ME.

41:22.080 --> 41:23.729
NO WOMAN IS GOING TO
LOOK AT US TWICE

41:23.780 --> 41:25.873
IF WE'RE SHARING OUR OFFICE
WITH THAT RIDICULOUS ADONIS.

41:25.910 --> 41:27.002
HE'S BETTER-LOOKING

41:27.050 --> 41:27.846
THAN BOTH OF US PUT TOGETHER.

41:27.880 --> 41:29.245
YEAH.

41:29.280 --> 41:30.747
I'M NOT DOING IT.

41:32.220 --> 41:33.539
GUS.

41:33.590 --> 41:36.058
YOU KNOW I CAN'T FIRE PEOPLE.

41:36.090 --> 41:37.557
THEY LOOK TOO SAD.

41:37.590 --> 41:38.579
THIS WAS YOUR IDEA.

41:38.630 --> 41:39.619
FIGURE IT OUT.

41:48.030 --> 41:49.839
[KEYBOARD TAPPING]

41:56.710 --> 41:58.109
[BUZZING]

42:01.750 --> 42:03.570
[DOOR CLOSES]

42:06.790 --> 42:11.056
[***]

42:13.790 --> 42:17.157
* IN BETWEEN THE LINES
THERE'S A LOT OF OBSCURITY *

42:17.200 --> 42:20.624
* I'M NOT INCLINED
TO RESIGN TO MATURITY *

42:20.670 --> 42:23.764
* IF IT'S ALL RIGHT
THEN YOU'RE ALL WRONG *

42:23.800 --> 42:28.828
* BUT WHY BOUNCE AROUND
TO THE SAME DAMN SONG? *

42:28.880 --> 42:32.873
* YOU'D RATHER RUN
WHEN YOU CAN CRAWL *

42:35.150 --> 42:38.142
* I KNOW YOU KNOW
THAT I'M NOT TELLING THE TRUTH *

42:38.180 --> 42:41.684
* I KNOW YOU KNOW
THEY JUST DON'T HAVE ANY PROOF *

42:41.720 --> 42:44.621
* EMBRACE THE DECEPTION
LEARN HOW TO BEND *

42:44.660 --> 42:46.628
* YOUR WORST INHIBITIONS

42:46.660 --> 42:49.026
* THEY WILL PSYCH YOU OUT
IN THE END *

42:49.060 --> 42:52.359
* I KNOW YOU KNOW

42:52.400 --> 42:55.836
* I KNOW YOU KNOW *
